(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, "enemy" for the purposes of this Act means— (a) any State, or Sovereign of a State, at war with the Republic; (b) any individual resident in enemy territory ; (c) any body of persons (whether corporate or unincorporate) carrying on business in any place, if and so long as the body is controlled by a person who, under this section, is an enemy; (d) any body of persons constituted or incorporated in, or under the laws of, a State at war with the Republic; and (e) as respects any business carried on in enemy territory , any individual or body of persons (whether corporate or unincorporate) carrying on that business; but does not include any individual by reason only that he is an enemy subject .
