(2) The President may by order direct that any person specified in the order shall, for the purposes of this Act, be deemed to be, while so specified, an enemy: Provided that, notwithstanding the provisions of the Interpretation and General Provisions Act, the names of any persons so specified in any such order as aforesaid shall be deemed to have been published when a copy of such order has been deposited at the office of the Custodian of Enemy Property, where it may be inspected free of charge by members of the public at any time during the usual Government office hours. [As amended by No. 34 of 1947 and S.I. No. 5 of 1965] [Cap. 2]
